# Shared Boundary Rules

## Intent
Keep `packages/shared` as platform-agnostic domain logic consumed by web and mobile.

## Shared Package Must Include
- API clients/wrappers (GetStream wrappers, HTTP client abstractions).
- Domain models, DTOs, validation, serialization, constants, error codes.
- Platform-agnostic state/domain logic.
- Reusable hooks that do not depend on DOM or React Native APIs.

## Boundary Rules
- No `window`, `document`, or React Native module imports in `packages/shared`.
- Put side effects behind adapter interfaces (storage, notifications, device capabilities).
- Export public API only from package entry points (`src/index.ts` style boundary).
- Shared package must not import from web or mobile packages.

## Testing Rules
- Shared logic requires unit tests.
- Adapter contracts require integration tests in consuming packages.

## Prohibited
- UI components in `packages/shared`.
- Leaking platform-specific dependencies into shared transitive graph.